<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">The specific epithet is a noun in the genitive case honouring Sidnei Mateus, for his friendship and prolific fieldwork.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">The male can be distinguished from its congeners by the combination of: wing without markings; tergite IX with pair of rounded lobes submedially with about 14 long setae; anal point parallel-sided; superior volsella small, subtriangular, projecting medially, with 2 setae on tubercles apically.</paragraph>
